00:34:26.159 --> 00:34:28.534
can make them into the identity
by integrating over this.

00:34:28.534 --> 00:34:31.500
But once I pull this
through and put it over

00:34:31.500 --> 00:34:32.530
on the right hand side--

00:34:32.530 --> 00:34:35.174
left hand side, then you have
to leave these delta functions

00:34:35.174 --> 00:34:35.730
there.

00:34:35.730 --> 00:34:37.439
They're specifying
the measurement.

00:34:40.980 --> 00:34:47.699
So this is a total n
collinear momentum,

00:34:47.699 --> 00:34:54.819
and this is the total
ultra soft in hemisphere A.

00:34:54.819 --> 00:34:57.480
That's what the A means.

00:34:57.480 --> 00:35:00.840
So I divided everything into
hemisphere A and B. Obviously,

00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:02.340
all the n collinear
particles, which

00:35:02.340 --> 00:35:04.860
