00:35:15.240 --> 00:35:20.720
I can also expand
these delta functions,

00:35:20.720 --> 00:35:23.418
and I only need to keep the
leading order piece if we're

00:35:23.418 --> 00:35:24.460
working at leading order.

00:35:38.100 --> 00:35:40.570
And so the leading order
pieces are as follows.

00:35:40.570 --> 00:35:43.410
There's an order of
lambda squared piece.

00:35:43.410 --> 00:35:44.383
This is lambda squared.

00:35:44.383 --> 00:35:46.050
There's an order of
lambda squared piece

00:35:46.050 --> 00:35:47.950
from the collinear
momentum squared,

00:35:47.950 --> 00:35:50.220
and since this is a
total collinear momentum,

00:35:50.220 --> 00:35:52.050
it can involve multiple
massless particles.

00:35:52.050 --> 00:35:53.610
It doesn't have to be zero.

00:35:53.610 --> 00:35:56.040
And then there's a cross
term between the softs

00:35:56.040 --> 00:35:56.790
and the collinear.

00:35:56.790 --> 00:35:58.082
It's also order lambda squared.

00:35:58.082 --> 00:36:00.440
This order one.

00:36:00.440 --> 00:36:02.850
And this is order
lambda squared,

00:36:02.850 --> 00:36:04.293
and that term's the same size.

00:36:04.293 --> 00:36:06.210
And then all the other
terms are higher order.

00:36:08.770 --> 00:36:11.560
These terms are suppressed,
so this is really

00:36:11.560 --> 00:36:12.970
all I need to keep.

00:36:12.970 --> 00:36:17.620
There's also something
else that effectively we've

00:36:17.620 --> 00:36:20.448
